. Prolonged exposure to these toxins can also lead to kidney damage due to the plant's ability to interfere with the normal functioning of the kidneys, ultimately causing the body to lose essential water and salts, resulting in dehydration. This is because the toxins in the plant can damage the renal tubules and impair the kidneys' ability to filter waste products from the blood. Furthermore, the loss of water and salts through diarrhea and vomiting can exacerbate dehydration, making it essential to handle the plant with care and avoid ingesting its parts altogether.", "category-action": "anti-inflammatory", "category_action": "antimicrobial"}